"Overall:  This beer rocks! definitely a sipper, but after taking your first sip you want the experience to last as long as possible.  This and Good Gourd by Cigar City are the 2 best beers I have ever had that prominently incorporate pumpkin into the style.  They are totally different styles so I don't want to compare apples with oranges, but if you enjoy pumpkin beer styles, don't hesitate to pick this up"
""
""
"Picked this up in a great trade with Jonathan!  Dark brown, nearly black pour with a nice two finger beige head with nice retention and great lacing.  The nose is amazing with huge bourbon and dark fruit notes along with hints of dark chocolate, raisins, molasses, cocoa, vanilla, and oak.  The taste is extremely bold with huge bourbon barrel notes front and center.  Tons of dark fruits, especially raisins, along with hints of molasses, dark chocolate, oak, vanilla, toffee, maple, and subtle, earthy pumpkin.  Surprisingly, the pumpkin pie spices are not overpowered by the booze. The cinnamon, nutmeg, clove, and allspice really emerge as it comes to temp.  The mouthfeel is thick and syrupy and extremely rich with an awesome warming finish.  With that said, considering the 17.22% ABV, it's way more drinkable than expected.  Sure, it's definitely a sipper, but no wheres near as hot and harsh as some reviewers made it out to be.  Overall, this was a complex, bold, and flavorful beer.  Highly recommended!"
