"My first thought was 'points for originality', but the boozy, syrupy palate-overload seems to balance out over progressive sips.  Definitely a one of kind brew."
"A little more porter chocolate here, but man oh man you will not miss the fact that this is north of 17% ABV. Alcohol hot hot heat dominate though, even sipping it slowly. getting past that though, there is the aforementioned chocolate and hints of coffee, but that same blend of vanilla from the barrel bleeding into the vanilla of the porter and the creamy sweet of pumpkin meat.  Round and smoothe once you get past the overwhelming alcohol. I like most of the underlying flavours. I suppose I would consider laying it down for a couple of years, but I would worry that the underlying pumpkin from which much of the pleasure derives might dissipate. As it is it's still far too hot to truly enjoy/appreciate now. Lots of tasty complex flavours, just so overshadowed by the boozahol..."
