"A truly massive beer - a bit too big for its own good, even. Nose is nothing but deep, syrupy scents of baked figs, molasses, and spiced rum, bearing no resemblance to a porter whatsoever (I'm thinking Belgian quad or BSDA). Initial tastes follow suit but carry a slow whiskey burn on top of the residual sugars. Get past that, though, and the beer opens up with notes of coconut, almond, and the toasted, dark-chocolate grain taste of an imperial porter, along with just the slightest notes of ginger and pumpkin purée. Overall, this one is enjoyable (for being such a big beer), but I'd give it at least another 6 months in the bottle to mellow out. Personally, I think a year would be perfect. Cheers!"
