"A great beer. Best pumpkin beer I have had."
"Pours a cola color with tan head and decent retention.  The nose is intense.  Heavy spice and barrel notes up front with a considerable amount of booziness.  Cinnamon is the strongest of the spices with some nutmeg and allspice in the back.  The bourbon barrel brings heavy vanilla and char.  The spice and barrel are more prominent than the porter base.  Hints of chocolate are present but are basically buried.  The taste is a cinnamon bomb with heavy sweetness.  Notes of caramelized pumpkin, brown sugar, vanilla, and barrel char all come through.  The alcohol brings some warmth to the finish.  While this is sweet, the sweetness is relatively in check considering the high abv.  Overall, a pretty intriguing brew.  The spice profile doesn't scream pumpkin as it leans so heavily to the cinnamon side of things.  I wish there was more porter character here, perhaps some chocolate or roast."
