"Looks great, a nice tidy white head, not quite opaque. The color of a pecan pie. Smells like a glass of liqueur - not bourbon, exactly, but something sweeter and more outre. The pumpkin spice flavor comes through in a big way, but it was welcome. On the first couple of sips, I couldn't taste the bourbon because it was so hot, but after it warmed in the glass for a few minutes, there was an exquisite velvety bourbon flavor that hit hard at the beginning, and slowly gave way to the imperial porter's maltiness. I'd definitely drink this again if someone else would foot the bill. (I assume these bottles are cheaper for CO locals to buy, but my single 12 oz. bottle cost me $12.99.)"
